-- Creditors Back KPMG Plans for MF Global’s U.K. Administration
-- B y   K i t   C h e l l e l
-- 2012-01-09T16:40:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-09/creditors-back-kpmg-plans-for-mf-global-s-u-k-administration.html
MF Global Holding Ltd.’s U.K. unit’s
clients and creditors voted “overwhelmingly” in favor of
proposals for the administration of the failed broker, KPMG LLP
partner Richard Heis said of  unit had voted  “All of the proposals have been overwhelmingly voted in
favor of,” Heis said at a meeting in  London  today. Votes on who
should be appointed to a new creditors committee hadn’t  been
counted, Heis said.  KPMG was appointed as special administrator of MF Global
U.K. Ltd. on Oct. 31, in the first use of a new program for
winding up financial firms.  To contact the reporter on this story:
